Class CoreCollectors

java.lang.Object
org.krmdemo.techlabs.core.utils.CoreCollectors
public class CoreCollectors extends Object
A factory of Collectors that allows to collect the stream of values into linked or sorted sets and the stream of entries and any other types into the linked or the sorted map. An enumeration MergeFunction could be used to handle the entries with the same key.

      Returns:
      a Collector which collects all the input elements into a LinkedHashSet.

      Returns:
      a Collector, which collects all the input elements into a TreeSet

    • toSortedMap

      public static <K,U> Collector<Map.Entry<K,U>, ?, NavigableMap<K,U>> toSortedMap()
      The same as JDK's toMap(...), but the elements of collecting stream are required to be of type Map.Entry, and the produced sorted-map accepts them one by one like if the method Map.putAll(Map) would be invoked (the latest entries overwrite the existing ones).
      Type Parameters:
      K - the type of key for entries in input stream
      U - the type of value for entries in input stream
      Returns:
      a Collector, which collects all the input elements into a TreeMap

    • toSortedMap

      public static <K,V,U> Collector<Map.Entry<K,V>, ?, NavigableMap<K,U>> toSortedMap(Function<Map.Entry<K,V>, U> valueMapper)
      The same as toSortedMap(), but the parameter valueMapper allows to transform the whole input entry of type Map.Entry<K,V> into the value of output entry of type Map.Entry<K,U>, and the key of input entry remains the same in output one.
      the brief summary is:
      • valueMapper function accepts Map.Entry<K,V> and returns <U>
      Type Parameters:
      K - the type of key for entries in input and output streams
      V - the type of value for entries in output stream
      U - the type of value for entries in input stream
      Parameters:
      valueMapper - the function to transform the value
      Returns:
      a Collector that which collects all the input elements into a TreeMap

    • toSortedMap

      public static <T,K,U> Collector<T, ?, NavigableMap<K,U>> toSortedMap(Function<? super T, ? extends K> keyMapper, Function<? super T, ? extends U> valueMapper)
      The same as JDK's toMap(...), but produces TreeMap with overwriting the duplicates.
      the brief summary is:
      • keyMapper function accepts <T> and returns the type of entry-key <K>
      • valueMapper function accepts <T> and returns the type of entry-value <U>
      Type Parameters:
      T - the type of the input elements
      K - the output type of the key-mapping function
      U - the output type of the value-mapping function
      Parameters:
      keyMapper - a key-mapping function to produce keys
      valueMapper - a value-mapping function to produce values
      Returns:
      a Collector that collects elements into a NavigableMap, whose keys are the result of applying a keyMapper function to the input elements, and whose values are the result of applying a valueMapper function to all input elements equal to the key and overwriting the existing values with new ones (according to enum-value OVERWRITE).

    • toSortedMap

      public static <T,K,U> Collector<T, ?, NavigableMap<K,U>> toSortedMap(Function<? super T, ? extends K> keyMapper, Function<? super T, ? extends U> valueMapper, MergeFunction mergeFunction)
      The same as toSortedMap(keyMapper,valueMapper), but allows to handle duplicates with mergeFunction parameter.
      the brief summary is:
      • keyMapper function accepts <T> and returns the type of entry-key <K>
      • valueMapper function accepts <T> and returns the type of entry-value <U>
      Type Parameters:
      T - the type of the input elements
      K - the output type of the key-mapping function
      U - the output type of the value-mapping function
      Parameters:
      keyMapper - a key-mapping function to produce keys
      valueMapper - a value-mapping function to produce values
      mergeFunction - one of values that are represented by MergeFunction-enum
      Returns:
      a Collector, that collects elements into a TreeMap, whose keys are the result of applying a keyMapper function to the input elements, and whose values are the result of applying a valueMapper function to all input elements equal to the key and combining them using the mergeFunction.
